  "sections": {
    "Background": {
      "text": "Primary\nHSV-1\ninfection of lips, gingiva, and tongue\nHSV-2 associated with genital disease\nUsually occurs in childhood\n[1]\n90% of population is seropositive by age 40\n[1]\nTreatment does not affect dormant virus in nerve ganglions → recurrent disease remains possible",
      "subsections": {},
      "tables": [],
      "links": [
        {
          "text": "HSV-1",
          "url": "https://wikem.org/wiki/HSV-1"
        }
      ]
    },
    "Clinical_Features": {
      "text": "Prodrome of\nfever\n,\nmyalgias\n, and cervical\nlymphadenopathy\n[2]\nPainful vesicular and/or ulcerative lesions of mucocutaneous areas (non-keratinized mucosa)\nCan be extremely painful and → odynophagia\nLasts approximately 1-4 weeks without treatment, course shortened with treatment",
      "subsections": {},
      "tables": [],
      "links": [
        {
          "text": "fever",
          "url": "https://wikem.org/wiki/Fever"
        },
        {
          "text": "myalgias",
          "url": "https://wikem.org/wiki/Myalgia"
        },
        {
          "text": "lymphadenopathy",
          "url": "https://wikem.org/wiki/Lymphadenopathy"
        }
      ]
    },
